review_blob: On tap. Dark and thick. Aroma of sweet molasses and peat smoke. Dark malt is the predominant taste with notes of coffee and raisins. Thick coating palate.
On tap. Notes of brittle, hard candy, maple syrup, coffee, and oak. A rich sweetness and great finish. Nice and warning.
Bottle. Pours a thick medium brown with a creamy head. Aromas of malt, pine, and brown sugar. Very sweet with noticeable bitterness. Coats the mouth nicely. A good slow sipping beer.
Bottle. Bronze color with light head. Buttery, melon, dough. Mild hops with a smooth finish.
Bottle. Very fruity and floral aroma. Sweet and very full -flavored. Tart, herbal, with flavors reminiscent of stuffing. Good carbonation and a slightly sour finish.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Venus - The Bringer Of Peace

review_blob: Bottle. Pours a clear dark brown with little head. Grainy hop aromas. Bitterness opens up early. Notes of roasted grain, lots of grapefruit, with a fruity edge. Bitter finish.
beer_name: Founders Dark Penance Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: On tap. Clear burgundy. Hay, grain, and dried fruit aromas. Taste matches the aroma. Thick and very sweet, with the strength masked.
On tap. Clear golden, light head. Lots of peat. Dough, honey, and cranberries also present. Unusual, almost sour finish.
beer_name: Hof Ten Dormaal BA Project 2013 (Blond Ale) No. 8 Port Charlotte

review_blob: Deep caramel color. Bold, clean hop aromas. Nice balance of sweet malt and floral hops. Lots of grassy hops, but only mild bitterness. Good mouthfeel and pleasant finish.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Mars - The Bringer Of War

review_blob: Deep red color with minimal head. Mild yeast aroma with sweet fruit notes. Lots of malt, stone fruit, and syrup notes. Creamy mouthful balanced with carbonation levels. Rich flavor and smooth finish.
beer_name: Goose Island Gormans Biere de Garde

review_blob: Bottle. Yellow to gold appearance with an airy head. Buttery, with notes of apple, guava, and papaya. Finishes with lemon, pepper, and a distinct tartness.

Opaque black. Rich, sweet, smoky aroma. Raisins, prunes, and molasses up front. Smoky peat and cocoa balance out the sweetness at the end. A big well-balanced beer with a lot of flavor. Very rich - excellent!
Reddish brown color with creamy head and nice lacing. Aromas of wood, plums, figs, and citrus. Strong flavor with noticeable alcohol up front.
Bottle. Bright yellow color with very little head. Aromas of wine grapes, lime, and hops. Strong carbonation and a slightly bitter, almost sour finish. Very crisp and refreshing.

Bottle. Slightly cloudy straw color with a foamy white head. Yeast, dough, and cranberries on the nose. Taste is similar with a tart finish. Good body and the carbonation makes for a crisp and refreshing palate.
Bottle. Deep amber with a thin creamy head. Aroma is lemon, travertine, and grain. Very full, creamy mouthful. Lots of malt. Nicely balanced with a great finish.
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: On tap. Thick and black with a light residual head. Butterscotch and vanilla aromas hit first, followed by bourbon. Taste is similar with added notes of licorice, prunes, and oak. Moderate palate with decent carbonation. Finish is sweet and almost a bit sour.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Very dark pour. Lots of dark malt, chocolate, figs, ripe stone fruit, and bourbon. Quite sweet with a dark malt bitterness. Very complex and strong.
beer_name: Port Brewing Santas Little Helper - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Bottle. Dark cola color with a moderate head. Caramel with mild nutty and smoky flavors. Sweet with a creamy palate and nice finish.
beer_name: Three Floyds Robert The Bruce Scottish Ale

review_blob: On tap. Ruddy color. Caramel, malts, and mushrooms. Sweet, smooth palate. Unusual finish.
Can. Pale yellow with a foamy head. Mild fruity and yeasty aroma. Flavor has a hint of watermelon. Bright and refreshing.
Bottle. Clear copper color with a light head. Lemon, grass, smoke, and yeast. Smoky bitter finish. Unusual and good.
beer_name: Stone Matts Burning Rosids Imperial Cherry Wood Smoked Saison

review_blob: Bottle. Dark reddish-brown with very little head. Molasses and root vegetables. Mild nuttiness and bitterness at the end.
On tap. Almost black with a light head and good lacing. Lots of chocolate, vanilla, grain and a good bit of bourbon. Rich and creamy. A big bold beer.
On tap. Pours an orange - amber color with a creamy head. Grain, floral hops, and almonds on the nose. Flavor pulls out the almonds and honey with a sweet citrus finish.

Bottle. Clear copper color with a foamy head. Grapefruit and brown sugar on the nose. Flavor is similar with the malts and mild oakiness providing a good balance to the hops. Rich with a pleasant finish.
On tap. Almost black without much head. Heavy butterscotch aroma. Taste is heavy on the butterscotch and caramel with vanilla and smoke. Unusual mix of sweet and bitter.
beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Howler from Latitude 42. Bright amber color and a light tan head. Nice blend of malts and hops. Notes of dough and toast. Very creamy palate and a clean flavorful finish.
beer_name: Latitude 42 Red Beards India Red Ale

review_blob: On tap. Aroma and taste have lots of blueberries and oak. Nice sweetness and carbonation. A bit of tartness right at the end. Very complex and unusual, in a really good way.
On tap. Dark brown with a large coffee head. Dark malts are balanced nicely with a hefty side of hops. Nice flavor profile with notes of coffee and grain, and a rich palate.
On tap. Dark with a creamy head and nice lacing. Lots of coffee and cacao nibs. Good flavor with a slightly light palate.
Murky brown with a thin head. Cereal, brown sugar, and dates. Smooth, sweet and quite refreshing for a stronger beer.
beer_name: Right Brain IGOR Takes A Digger Imperial Brown Ale

review_blob: On tap. Clear pilsner color. Tart fruit notes with a refreshing hoppy finish. Very drinkable.
Bottle. Dark cola color with no head. Toasted oak, peanuts, chocolate, and just a touch of bourbon. Rich palate, light carbonation. Really nice finish and complex flavor profile.
beer_name: Thirsty Dog Bourbon Barrel Aged Siberian Night

review_blob: On tap. Clear golden orange with light lacing. Aromas of citrus and tropical fruits. Clean palate with a bitter vegetable finish.
beer_name: New Belgium / Cigar City Lips of Faith - Anaheim & Marash Chili Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Clear ruddy amber with a light head. Aromas of dough, grain, and grass. Taste is similar with nutty notes. Sweet with a light palate and a fruity, almost sour finish.
Bottle. Clear chocolate color with a creamy head. Bananas, raisins, plums, molasses, and brown sugar. Creamy palate with a smooth, sweet finish. Excellent!
Very dark, not overly viscous pour. Chocolate, wood, resin, and grain. Highly carbonated. Cacao bitterness at the end.

Deep brown with a thin tan head. Aromas of fruity esters, yeast, honey, and plums. Taste matches the aroma with the addition of roasted coffee notes. Rich palate with a mild tart finish and a good lingering flavor.
Clear orange-gold color. Nicely balanced. Sweet with notes of honey and toast, and lots of citrus, from tangerine to grapefruit. The hop kick at the end is noticeable, but not overwhelming.
Deep amber color. Clove and gingerbread on the nose. Creamy mouthfeel and well hidden alcohol. Flavor has notes of red berries and sugar candy.
Bottle. Pours a muddy amber-brown color with a head. Apple and coffee on the nose. Chocolate and apple flavors, with roasted malt and spices. Quite sweet and the alcohol is well hidden.
Bottle. Dark brown with a creamy head. Chocolate, wild blueberries, elderberries, oak, and cork. Very smooth with a silky mouthfeel.
Bottle. Clear burgundy color with a bubbly beige head. Sweet aroma with oak and alcohol notes. Flavor if died fruit, smoke, oak, tobacco, and caramel. Alcohol is strong as is the carbonation.

Bottle. Pours a murky russet color with a creamy white head. Aromas of floral hops and sugar candy. Flavor is biscuit, grass, and malt with a strong grapefruit rind finish. Very bitter as expected, but has a lot of flavor.

Bottle. 2013 vintage. Prune color with almost no head. Wine, tobacco, and alcohol on the nose. Taste is port, dark dried fruit, tobacco, smoke, and prunes. Sweet, smooth and a great mouthfeel. Alcohol presence is notable, but a very nice finish. Very complex. Outstanding beer!
Bottle. Bright gold color with a creamy white head. Notes of dough and cranberries. Sweet with a slight sour edge. Crisp carbonation and a very pleasant finish. Excellent strong golden ale.
Bottle. Dark chocolate color with a cinnamon head. Not much oak. Some smokiness, with a lot of dark, heavy malt. Full body. Smooth cocoa finish with a slightly bitter edge.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Bottle. Bright gold color with a thin pale head. Citrus, especially grapefruit, some resin, and straw. Sweet with a strong hop presence. Good mouthful and a clean finish.
Bottle. Clear amber color with a creamy head. Notes of caramel, bread, and nuts. Sweet and nice carbonation, but the finish is slightly bland. Quite good for the style.
